text: The Eirunepe snouted tree frog (Scinax garbei) is a frog that lives in Venezuela, Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, and Brazil. Scientists have seen it as high as 700 meters above sea level. The adult male frog is 42 to 46 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is 48 mm. They are brown or light brown with darker brown marks on the back. They have green color on parts of their legs. They belly is white. This frog lives in trees and looks for food at night. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Scinax garbei
